# Restaurant Standards — Cursor Rules

## Project
- Name: Restaurant Standards
- Live URL: restaurantstandards.com
- Local folder: service-standards-app
- GitHub: https://github.com/Dereks-Projects/restaurant-service-standards
- Framework: Next.js 16.1.6 (App Router)
- Deployment: git push to main → Vercel auto-deploys
- DNS: GoDaddy → Vercel (never touch DNS)

## Non-Negotiable Rules
- CSS Modules only — never Tailwind, never inline styles
- pnpm only — never npm or yarn
- Never modify src/proxy.js without a confirmed diagnosis
- Never modify src/config/siteConfig.js structure — only values
- All nav and branding changes start in src/config/siteConfig.js
- Always provide complete files — never partial snippets or surgical edits
- Always specify exact folder and filename before every file
- Run pnpm build before every deployment — must be clean

## Environment
- Windows / VS Code or Cursor / PowerShell
- PowerShell syntax only (e.g., Remove-Item -Recurse -Force, not rm -rf)
- pnpm as package manager

## Architecture
- src/app/ — all pages (Next.js App Router)
- src/components/ — reusable UI components
- src/config/siteConfig.js — all branding, nav, links
- src/data/ — all JSON content files
- src/lib/sanity.js — Sanity CMS client
- src/proxy.js — geo-blocking (RU, CN) — do not touch
- public/ — static assets, images, favicon, social card

## Design System
- Background: #2a2a2a
- Surface: #3a3a3a
- Accent (gold): #e8c547
- Text: #f0f0f0
- Muted text: #a8a8a8
- Font: Inter (Google Fonts)
- Border radius: 8px / 12px / 16px
- Mobile breakpoint: 769px
- Mobile-first — desktop overrides use min-width: 769px at bottom of CSS files

## Key Files
- src/app/layout.js — root layout, SEO metadata, Google Analytics G-KV806MZ0LT
- src/app/page.js — homepage
- src/app/operators/page.js — business-facing operators page
- src/app/api/agent/route.js — OpenAI GPT-4o-mini endpoint, rate limited
- src/app/robots.js — auto-generates /robots.txt
- src/app/sitemap.js — auto-generates /sitemap.xml
- src/app/not-found.js — custom 404 page

## Environment Variables
- OPENAI_API_KEY — OpenAI API key (server-side only)
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SANITY_PROJECT_ID — 21zbxo34

## Developer Context
- Derek Engles is a novice coder with no formal CS background
- Explain what and why in plain language before showing code
- Use restaurant and hospitality analogies for technical concepts
- One step at a time — wait for confirmation before the next step
- Never assume prior knowledge of any technical concept
